# <type>: <short summary (50 chars max)>
#
# <body - explain what and why, not how (wrap at 72 chars)>
#
# <footer - reference issues, breaking changes, etc.>

# --- COMMIT MESSAGE GUIDELINES ---
#
# Type (required):
#   feat:     New feature
#   fix:      Bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation only changes
#   style:    Code formatting (not visual style)
#   refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf:     Performance improvement
#   test:     Adding missing tests
#   chore:    Build process, dependencies, tooling
#
# Subject line (required):
#   - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
#   - Don't capitalize first letter
#   - No period at the end
#   - Max 50 characters
#
# Body (optional):
#   - Explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#   - Separate from subject with blank line
#
# Footer (optional):
#   - Reference issues: "Fixes #123" or "Closes #456"
#   - Breaking changes: "BREAKING CHANGE: description"
#
# Examples:
#   feat: add double jump mechanic
#
#   fix: prevent player from falling through platforms
#
#   docs: update README with new controls
#
#   refactor: extract camera logic into separate method
#
# Remove all comment lines before committing
